$ apigear --help
ApiGear allows you to describe interfaces and generate instrumented SDKs out of the descriptions.

Usage:
  apigear [command]

Available Commands:
  check       check document
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  config      commands related to application configuration
  doc         exports cli docs as markdown
  help        Help about any command
  json2yaml   convert json doc to yaml doc
  monitor     A brief description of your command
  project     Manages project creation and management
  sdk         generates sdk
  simulate    A brief description of your command
  tpl         manage code generation templates
  yaml2json   convert yaml doc to json doc

Flags:
      --config string   config file (default is $HOME/.apigear.yaml)
      --dry-run         dry-run
      --env string      environment (development, production, staging) (default "development")
  -h, --help            help for apigear
  -v, --verbose         verbose output
      --version         version for apigear

Use "apigear [command] --help" for more information about a command.
